    <artifactId>blindbean-junit</artifactId>
    <name>BlindBean JUnit Support</name>
    <description>@BlindBeanTest and the JUnit 5 extension that manages a BlindContext per test. A
        separate module now, so a consumer only pulls JUnit onto its own path if it uses the
        extension — the main runtime no longer carries a provided-scope JUnit.</description>
